HLS 26RS-265 ORIGINAL
HB NO. 65
Present law requires that a public employee receive a minimum of one hour of education and
training on preventing sexual harassment during each full calendar year of his public
employment.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law requires that an elected official receive a minimum of one hour of education and
training on preventing sexual harassment during each full calendar year of his term of office.
Proposed law requires that an elected official receive a minimum of one hour of education
and training on preventing sexual harassment during his term in office.
(Amends R.S. 42:343(A)(1))
